Justify RAW_PTR_EXCLUSION for FeatureData
The pointer member of FeatureData only ever points at statically-allocated memory, and hence cannot dangle. This means that we don't need the extra overhead of rewriting it to a raw_ptr. Since FeatureData exists entirely in one cc file, the chances of this ever changing are very low.
